issue.title: Update nttc.dm

labels.name: On Hold
labels.description: Its gonna be a while before this is reviewed

issue.body:
## What Does This PR Do
Tweaks the existing NTTC file slightly so it accounts for the departmental color and bold value for: Acting Head titles and their alternative spellings, some of the most common Admin event jobs, one missing alternative job title (Pathologist) that I am guessing was forgotten during the removal of NTSL, and one of the most common service job titles.

## Why It's Good For The Game

Acting Heads are currently shown on the comms as default-green, and are not emboldened when they speak.
This is especially egregious for the "Acting Captain" job title which should be the most important voice on the station (until the arrival of the assigned Captain), and yet if they are asking for help or ordering for something to happen, not only is their voice completely unamplified, but even the distinctive deep blue color of command is missing from their name/title.
It's even worse when you consider that the Acting Captain is always an existing Head, so by accepting the highest-responsibility job on the station, they are actually forfeiting their distinctive color and emboldened voice.

Additionally, it adds a color (and emboldening when applicable) to the most common admin-spawned event characters that are often found on station: Nanotrasen Financial Officer, Ambassador, VIP


## Images of changes
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32230667/200134930-2b1bed6a-1fbc-405b-9a2b-41b75363af00.png)

## Testing
Changed job title to match the added titles.
Typed in common and departmental channels to test
Observed the presence of departmental color, and boldening when the speaker is considered in a "command" role

## Changelog
:cl:
add: Acting Heads' radio messages now have the departmental color and bold formatting when applicable.
add: Nanotrasen Financial Officer, VIP, Ambassador and Sous-Chef job titles added to the radio message formatting rules
fix: fixed an oversight that prevented Pathologist from being treated with the same comms formatting rules as Virologist
/:cl:

issue.title: Changes how the garbage subsystem queue stores and processes info

labels.name: On Hold
labels.description: Its gonna be a while before this is reviewed

issue.body:
<!-- Write **BELOW** The Headers and **ABOVE** The comments else it may not be viewable. -->
<!-- You can view Contributing.MD for a detailed description of the pull request process. -->

## What Does This PR Do
The way """we""" currently do it, each time you want to walk the queue you're forced to make a copy in memory of the whole thing

There's no real reason to want this, so it seems best to just avoid it entirely. It creates a TON of usage for no reason, and also risks a lot of overtime since you can't really batch a list copy like that.

So instead let's just iterate over the length of the queue, constant rather then O(N) time.

Similarly, rather then using an associated list in the form queue[ref] = gc time, we could store queue entries in what amounts to a tuple.

This means no associated list stuff, so the operation of queuing becomes cheaper, and pulling gc time similarly goes from O(log n) to constant time

I stole this work from myself and mso, tg pr 55595. I'm pring it here because I keep seeing affected complain about the garbage subsystem and he refuses to do it himself. No I don't have an ego problem I swear


## Why It's Good For The Game

Much faster, I can stop whining to affected

## Images of changes

I'll do you one better 

https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58055496/200111453-2b59b98e-c8f1-4bb1-a6fe-d9bce43d3541.mp4

## Testing

Detonated 3 100 dev bombs to fill the gc queue (note the lack of any cost at all), and set the queue timeout to 0 to flush the standard queue

## Changelog
N/A
